| # | Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Search input at top | `<input type="search" …>` rendered before the list |
| 2 | 300 ms debounce, no lodash | `useDebounce` custom hook using `setTimeout` / `clearTimeout` inside `useEffect` |
| 3 | Case-insensitive substring filter | `.toLowerCase().includes(debouncedQuery.toLowerCase())` |
| 4 | "Searching…" during debounce | `isPending = normalizedInput !== debouncedQuery` — true while the timeout hasn't fired |
| 5 | Empty input → show all | `debouncedQuery ? ITEMS.filter(…) : ITEMS` |
| 6 | Highlight matches | `HighlightedText` splits on a *capturing group* regex; odd indices are wrapped in `<mark>` |
| 7 | "No results" message | Rendered when `!isPending && debouncedQuery && filteredItems.length === 0` |
| 8 | Cleanup on unmount | `useEffect` returns `() => clearTimeout(timerId)` — fires on every re-render *and* on unmount |
| 9 | Edge cases | `inputValue.trim()` collapses whitespace-only to `""`; `escapeRegex()` neutralises `+`, `.`, `*`, `(`, etc. before passing to `new RegExp` |

### Key design decisions

- **Two state values, one hook** — `inputValue` updates on every keystroke (drives the input), `debouncedQuery` is what actually filters. The gap between them is what powers the "Searching…" indicator with zero extra state.
- **`split` with capturing group** — `"React".split(/(ea)/gi)` → `["R", "ea", "ct"]`. Odd indices are always the matched segments, so no secondary `.test()` call and no regex `lastIndex` issues.
- **`escapeRegex` before `new RegExp`** — prevents queries like `"C++"` or `"a.b"` from throwing or over-matching.

